meet%20higher%20investor%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20Klarna%20is%20public%2C%20here's%20what%20those%20top%2015%20shareholders'%20stakes%20are%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESequoia%20Capital%2C%20an%20investor%3A%20%243.5%20billion%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Reed%20sitting%20at%20a%20table%20with%20his%20arms%20crossed%2C%20wearing%20a%20blue%20zip-up%20sweater.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bf397f32af4d666ef77b81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Reed%3Cp%3ESequoia%20Capital%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20capital%20giant%20Sequoia%20Capital%20is%20the%20biggest%20benefactor%20of%20Klarna's%20IPO.%20The%20San%20Francisco-based%20firm%20Sequoia%20owned%2078.8%20million%20shares%2C%20or%20about%2020.1%25%20of%20the%20company%2C%20after%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-ceo-looked-up-sandhill-road-on-google-maps-before-sequoia-capital-investment-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESequoia%20first%20invested%20in%20Klarna%20in%202010%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20the%20company's%20%249%20million%20fundraise%20and%20contributing%20additional%20capital%20over%20numerous%20rounds%20in%20the%20following%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Sequoia%20partner%20Michael%20Moritz%20joined%20Klarna's%20board%20of%20directors%20at%20the%20firm's%202010%20investment%20and%20became%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20board%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Moritz%20stepped%20down%20from%20his%20investing%20position%20in%202023%2C%20Sequoia%20partner%20Matthew%20Morris%20joined%20Klarna's%20board%20to%20represent%20the%20firm.%20The%20following%20year%2C%20Morris%2C%20with%20Sequoia's%20backing%2C%20reportedly%20attempted%20to%20remove%20Moritz%20from%20the%20board%20altogether.%20After%20facing%20pushback%20from%20Klarna%20CEO%20Sebastian%20Siemiatkowsk